params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.stream_id
params.description: The ID of the stream. Only set on the first message, when a new stream was created.

params.name: data.stream_token
params.description: A token that represents the position of this response in the stream. This can be used by a client to resume the stream at this point. This field is always set.

params.name: data.write_results
params.description: The result of applying the writes. This i-th write result corresponds to the i-th write in the request.

params.name: data.commit_time
params.description: The time at which the commit occurred. Any read with an equal or greater read_time is guaranteed to see the effects of the write.
